<h2 id="org733adc0">Practical Info</h2>
<div class="outline-text-2" id="text-org733adc0">
<p>
The workshop will start October 24 at 9.30 am and end October 25 at
about 2 pm, so please consider this time window in planning your
trip to Rome. Please signal any time constraint you might have by
email to: villamassenziaworkshop-AT-sssup.it
</p>

<p>
The workshop venue is Villa Massenzia (address: via Appia Pignatelli
62, Rome). As it is a bit out of Rome city center, so a shuttle bus
will be made available by the organization from the metro station
called Arco di Travertino (Metro Line A), which is 8 metro stops
(10-15 minutes) from the Central train station (Stazione Termini,
line A and line B).
</p>

<p>
Please consider to book your hotels close to Metro Linee A stops, so
that you can easily reach the shuttle bus departure station.
</p>

<p>
The bus will leave at 8.45 am and 9.15 am on Thursday 24 and at 8.30
am on Friday 25. One of the organizers will coordinate departures at
Arco di Travertino Metro stop. We strongly recommend to take
advantage of this opportunity, and pleas signal if you do not think
to come by the shuttle bus. A shuttle bus returning from Villa
Massenzia to Arco di Travertino will also be available on Thursday
24 evening and on Friday 25 after the farewell lunch.
</p>

<p>
The organization covers coffee breaks and lunches on 24 and 25
October at Villa Massenzia, and a social dinner on 24 October in a
restaurant in the city center (yet to be defined). Please confirm
your participation to social dinner by email to:
villamassenziaworkshop-AT-sssup.it
</p>
